<item>
            <title>[LU-17718] Coverity: 424705 (String overflow) under upcall_cache.c</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17718</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;CID 424705:  Security best practices violations  (STRING_OVERFLOW)&lt;br/&gt;
/lustre/obdclass/upcall_cache.c: 187 in upcall_cache_set_upcall()&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;181     invalid:
182         OBD_FREE(upcall, count + 1);
183         return -EINVAL;
184     
185     valid:
186         down_write(&amp;amp;cache-&amp;gt;uc_upcall_rwsem);
  CID 424705:  Security best practices violations  (STRING_OVERFLOW)
  You might overrun the 1024-character fixed-size string &quot;cache-&amp;gt;uc_upcall&quot; by copying &quot;upcall&quot; without checking the length.
187         strcpy(cache-&amp;gt;uc_upcall, upcall);
188         up_write(&amp;amp;cache-&amp;gt;uc_upcall_rwsem);
189     
190         OBD_FREE(upcall, count + 1);
191         return 0;
192     }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
